                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d802">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">303.1111 M Nielsen, Niels/73: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Japan (<persName type="to">Grew</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-10-26T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 26, 1933—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>102. Your unnumbered [<hi rend="italic">167</hi>,] October 25, 11 p.m.<note
                        n="44" xml:id="d802fn44">Not printed.</note> Please express to Foreign
                    Office your Government’s appreciation of Japanese official assistance in
                    effecting release of Nielsen; also congratulations on escape of Torihata.
                    Department is instructing Peiping to make similar expression at Peiping and
                    Mukden.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
